profile_positions.description:
- Under the supervision of the Director of the Inspectorate or a designated Team Leader, supports the operational planning and on-site execution of OPCW inspections at a wide variety of industrial and military installations world-wide and performs the following duties:
•	Plans inspections, by: Supporting inspection preparations in relation to health and safety, logistical and administrative/confidentiality related matters;
•	Performs inspections, by: Performing engineering evaluations of industrial and military chemical installations to determine their consistency with their declared purpose and capacity; Conducting an evaluation of production and logistical records; Monitoring the destruction of chemical weapons at chemical weapon destruction facilities;
•	Reports on inspection activities by: Contributing to the writing of final inspection reports; Maintaining confidentiality in relation to inspection related information
Achievements: Being one of the seven inspectors promoted from being a Chemical Technologist/ inspector  to become a Chemical Technologist/Team Leader through a highly competitive process of interviews and performance appraisal, competing against over 100 inspectors from all over the world
